    "client_msg_id": "b6a5c206-7601-4fbb-b2de-ec06134625cf",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "So all comments are automatic trace statements.  That might teach people to avoid bad comment habits (like commenting out instead of deleting or wrapping in #define if your language supports that) but it also assumes that many comments are useful runtime information, which probably isn't true.  Basically I'm not sure why it's better or more clear than explicit traces, which can display dynamic runtime information and can also be read like comments when the code isn't running",
